RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 13800. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WICKOSITY saved ground, bid nearing the three eighths pole, drew aim three wide midway on the far turn and dueled for the lead later yards. ADARA stalked from the three path, challenged leaving the three eighths pole and took a slim lead inside the eighth, dug in leaving the far turn but was outfinished through later yards. CHROME HEIR settled off the rail, started a bid leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the four path, left the turn outside and finished well to take third later yards. OBOY raced with the pace inside, dueled CAN'T STOP MAXEY from the three eighths pole, ran briefly clear midway on the far turn but was met inside the eighth pole and flattened the final sixteenth. The latter raced with the pace two deep, dueled from the three eighths pole but faded at the rail on the far turn. UNKNOWN AGENDA raced well back and never factored. POINT US HOME lost traction at the break, showed no response and only galloped around.

ENTRY.NAME: Unknown Agenda
ENTRY.OWNER: JBD Ranch LLC and Jones Duane

ENTRY.NAME: Can't Stop Maxey
ENTRY.OWNER: A P Stable and Fox Tale Racing Stable

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BELIEVEINROCKNROLL took the lead leaving the seven sixteenths pole and set a pressured pace, dueled clear past the quarter and held on well with steady encouragement. BAYTOWN JAKESTER pressured the pace at mostly even terms inside, dropped back at the rail past the quarter pole but finished evenly to hold second. LION OF THE SEA chased inside, raced at the rail on the turn, entered the stretch in the three path and finished evenly. POLITICAL DECISION gave chase, rounded the turn about the three path and ran evenly in the lane. FOREVER THE BOSS chased through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn and showed little more. ADIOS SEE YA chased the leaders outside, raced in the six path of the turn and entered the stretch widest. ABOUT TO RAGE gave chase and rounded the turn about the five path.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRACE'S SECRET stalked four wide on the first turn, bid leaving the five sixteenths pole and raced close three wide on the far turn, drifted into the stretch but dug in for the lead later yards and ran clear under the wire. DIAL HER stalked three wide on the opening turn, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, took the lead two deep midway on the far turn, dug in under steady handling in the lane but relented later yards. MIZZEN tapered in to take the lead nearing the three quarter pole and rated the pace off the rail, came under pressure nearing the three eighths pole, was met at the rail midway on the far turn and flattened inside the eighth pole. TOUT ENSEMBLE rounded the first turn in the four path, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and showed little in the lane. VILLAREGGIA raced in the three path the first turn, gave chase from the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and showed little in the lane. DISTORTED SPLENDOR raced with the pace inside, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but faded at the rail into the far turn.

ENTRY.COMMENT: with pace inside,chased 7/16,faded rail into far turn

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JOHNNY SWISH rated close off the rail, challenged three wide nearing the three eighths pole, took the lead two deep passing the quarter pole, dueled clear midway on the far turn and was steadily handled through the lane. BET ON BITZ rounded the first turn in the three and four paths, started a bid toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the five path of the far turn and dueled through the stretch for second. STRONG HEART raced off the rail on the opening turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the four path and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. SCOOTSCOOT was rushed up and moved in to race with the pace two deep, came under pressure at the three eighths pole, gave up the lead at the rail passing the quarter pole and weakened in the lane. LET'S GET PHYSICAL settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase from the half mile pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and showed little in the lane. AMERICAN ROCKY saved ground, picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and showed little in the lane. POSTED raced with the pace inside, gave chase from the three eighths pole but faded at the rail on the far turn.

LEG UP rated close off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, took the lead two deep past the five sixteenths, drew clear into the far turn but was met past the eighth pole and relented the final sixteenth. SPECTACULO rounded the opening turn in the three path, bid from the three eighths pole, raced in range of the lead three wide on the far turn but flattened the final sixteenth. HOSTLER drew clear and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths pole, was met at the rail passing the five sixteenths, dropped back at the quarter and faded on the far turn. RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eli gibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHESAPEAKE CHARLIE rated close in the three and four paths, bid leaving the three eighths pole, took the lead three wide midway on the far turn, drew clear into the lane and held on; all out. RIGHTEOUS MAN settled off the rail, picked up the chase into the backstretch and improved five wide on the far turn, dueled clear in second mid-stretch and was gaining on the waning winner. SULEMAN saved ground, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, was eased to the six path on the far turn, left the turn outside and came along for third while gaining on the top two. BOSSY CAT rated close inside, bid leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail then flattened stride. STAVANGER settled in the four path, gave chase from the half mile pole and raced close four wide on the far turn, then weakened in the stretch. HE CAME TRUE rated close in the two and three path, challenged at even terms leaving the three eighths pole but steadied between horses in the vicinity of the five sixteenths pole, recovered stride through the far turn but showed little in the lane. URBAN WARRIOR angled to the inside and rated the pace, came under pressure and dueled at even terms from the three eighths pole, raced two deep on the far turn and weakened. BOOK OF DELANCEY showed little response.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 70. Allowance Purse 35100. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 25 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since January 25 Allowed 4 lbs. (Ra ces Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GREAT SPIRIT pressured the pace and took the lead at the five sixteenths pole, widened off the rail on the turn and was kept alert through the stretch. SLEWING chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn in the four path, was carried out leaving the turn but dug in to take second later yards. TIMETOGETUP chased the pace, rounded the turn in the six path, left the turn outside, finished well and just missed second. DIXIE YODELER gave chase, raced near the rail on the turn, was eased to the four path leaving the turn and finished evenly to pass rivals. WINDSOR'S PLAY chased inside, raced at the rail on the turn then flattened in the lane. CASTLE TOY set a pressured pace most of the opening quarter mile, but was met a the five sixteenths pole, raced near the rail on the turn and weakened in the lane. LEMONSONDESURPRISE chased, rounded the turn about the three path, drifted into the lane and weakened. EMBERLY chased the pace, rounded the turn off the rail and showed little in the lane. SIENTE LA BRISA chased inside, was blocked at the rail off the heels of Windsor's Play approaching the eighth pole and weakened. DIVA ROSE was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 9 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 45. Maiden Claiming Purse 13300. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHY LEA was roughed from tight quarters between horses into the first turn and ran in the three path through the turn, started a bid leaving the three eighths pole, raced close in the three path of the far turn, dug in for the lead late stretch and drew clear toward the wire. PRINCESS MIA ROSE took over while tapering to the inside and rated the pace, came under pressure nearing the three eighths pole, contested the edge nearest the rail on the far turn, was steadily handled leaving the turn, but relented late while able to hold second. CREDIT COMMITTEE rounded the first turn about the three path, gave chase into the backstretch, raced at the rail on the far turn and dueled through the stretch for second. CHANTILLY MOON (PER) rounded the first turn in the three path, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. OUR GOLDEN COLLEEN stalked off the rail the first turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced close two deep on the far turn but weakened nearing mid-stretch. HOLY HIP steadied at the start, raced well back in the five path on the first turn and could only improve her position. I'M SO EXTRA stalked four wide, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path of the far turn and weakened in the lane. AMERICAN LEGACY saved ground. T J STORM VISION became a bit edgy in the gate and steadied off the heels of Princess Mia Rose into the first turn, saved ground through the turn, picked up the chase from the three eighths pole but faded into the far turn and was eased.

ENTRY.NAME: Holy Hip
ENTRY.OWNER: C M Racing Stables LLC and Lewis Jalen
